
📂 Selection Sort in Python
Problem

Sort an array in ascending order using the Selection Sort algorithm.

Example

Input:

numbers = [18, 9, 27, 5]

Output:

[5, 9, 18, 27]
Algorithm
Assume the current element is the smallest.
Store its index in smallest_index.
Traverse the remaining unsorted part of the array.
Find the actual smallest element.
Swap it with the current position.
Repeat until the array is sorted.
Python Code
numbers = [18, 9, 27, 5]

for i in range(len(numbers)):
    smallest_index = i

    for j in range(i + 1, len(numbers)):
        if numbers[j] < numbers[smallest_index]:
            smallest_index = j

    numbers[i], numbers[smallest_index] = numbers[smallest_index], numbers[i]

print(numbers)
