Time Complexity

O(n²)

Reason:

Outer loop runs n times.
Inner loop searches the remaining unsorted elements.
Nested loops result in O(n²).
Space Complexity

O(1)

Reason:

Only a few extra variables (i, j, smallest_index) are used.

Interview Questions
Why is it called Selection Sort?

Because in every pass, it selects the smallest element from the unsorted part of the array.

Why do we use smallest_index instead of smallest?

We need the index to swap elements.

Why does the inner loop start from i + 1?

Because the current element is already assumed to be the smallest, so comparing it with itself is unnecessary.

Is Selection Sort stable?

❌ No.

Is Selection Sort an in-place algorithm?

✅ Yes.

